Setup:


    Install aws cli, to communicate with AWS via command line
    Install python if not installed
    Create new virtualenv and activate

>> mkdir ~/Envs
>> python3 -m venv ~/Envs/env01
>> source ~/Envs/env01/bin/activate

    Install ansible

>> pip install ansible

   

Use pip to install the EB CLI.

$ pip install awsebcli --upgrade --user

Verify that the EB CLI installed correctly.

$ eb --version
EB CLI 3.14.8 

>> Use pip to install the EB CLI.

$ pip install awsebcli --upgrade --user

Verify that the EB CLI installed correctly.

$ eb --version
EB CLI 3.14.8 

>> ansible-galaxy collection install community.aws
